    <a title="Diem Le" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7585876-diem-le"><img alt="Diem Le" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1328064892p2/7585876.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/976939455?book_show_action=true">Jun 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diem Le" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diem Le" href="/user/show/7585876-diem-le">Diem Le</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Diem by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/7459087-mary">Mary</a>
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer976939455" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11957867311840548754">This is the novel Goldfinch wishes it was.<br/><br/>Richard Rosso can turn a phrase like no other, and the section in which Ned lives with his father is perfection: funny, clever, witty, heartfelt...style AND substance, over and over and over again. This kind of writing is a true talent that is rarely found. So enjoyable that I tried to read through the section slowly in order to make it last. I would have given this book five stars (and I do not inflate grades!!), except the other sections are just not q</span>
  <span id="freeText11957867311840548754" style="display:none">This is the novel Goldfinch wishes it was.<br /><br />Richard Rosso can turn a phrase like no other, and the section in which Ned lives with his father is perfection: funny, clever, witty, heartfelt...style AND substance, over and over and over again. This kind of writing is a true talent that is rarely found. So enjoyable that I tried to read through the section slowly in order to make it last. I would have given this book five stars (and I do not inflate grades!!), except the other sections are just not quite as good (though still very good!) and a bit slow. I suppose perfection is hard to sustain!! Still: loved loved loved.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11957867311840548754" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

