        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3517302999" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18383916439722473409">My first Russo. This is exactly like making a list of the characteristics you want from the man you intend to marry and then you go ahead and marry and love to death the opposite type guy.<br/>The books and authors I seem to like most are ones with great plots, diverse developing characters and brilliant clever writing - thats my list. <br/>This book has a below average plot, full and rich characters going nowhere and not so academically speaking great writing. <br/>But I loved it! <br/>Russo gets small town. Hence</span>
  <span id="freeText18383916439722473409" style="display:none">My first Russo. This is exactly like making a list of the characteristics you want from the man you intend to marry and then you go ahead and marry and love to death the opposite type guy.<br />The books and authors I seem to like most are ones with great plots, diverse developing characters and brilliant clever writing - thats my list. <br />This book has a below average plot, full and rich characters going nowhere and not so academically speaking great writing. <br />But I loved it! <br />Russo gets small town. Hence the plot and characters going nowhere. The repetitive writing re-iterates the nature of the stories and people from these towns. The similes he uses to create the ambiance is just laugh out loud joy and the bantering makes one feel right there. And the plot. Well it was awesome. So much love, surprise and development. <br />Looking forward to much much more Russo. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18383916439722473409" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


